snippet: The Nusra Front for the People of the Levant, a group Western intelligence officials have linked to Al Qaeda, said its bombers struck a government compound on the outskirts of Damascus overnight.
abstract: Al Nursa Front for the People of the Levant, jihadist insurgent group that Western intelligence officials have linked to Al Qaeda, claims responsibility for multiple bombing by suicide attackers at an intelligence compound on the outskirts of Damascus; attack is second that the group has claimed to have carried out against a government facility in about a week.

byline.original: By ANNE BARNARD and CHRISTINE HAUSER
byline.contributor: Anne Barnard reported from Beirut, and Christine Hauser from New York. Hwaida Saad contributed reporting from Beirut, Ranya Kadri from Amman, Jordan, and Rick Gladstone from New York.

lead_paragraph: The Nusra Front for the People of the Levant, a group Western intelligence officials have linked to Al Qaeda, said its bombers struck a government compound on the outskirts of Damascus overnight.

headline.seo: Qaeda-Tied Group Claims Attack on Edge of Damascus
headline.main: Qaeda-Linked Group Claims Responsibility for Syrian Blasts
headline.print_headline: Group Tied to Al Qaeda Claims Attack on Compound Near Damascus
